<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Grindelia</i> <i>stricta</i> or another <i>Grindelia</i> species is dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i>, <i>Jaumea</i> <i>carnosa</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>arcticus</i>, <i>Limonium</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Sarcocornia</i> <i>pacifica</i> and <i>Triglochin</i> <i>maritima</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 2 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Slightly elevated or drier ground that is adjacent to coastal dunes, salt marshes, or alkaline marshes, including bluffs, levees, and road margins. The USACE Wetland Plant List (2020 national list) recognizes <i>Grindelia stricta</i> as FACW. </div>
</div>

		
